<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<h1>HTML Events</h1>
<h2>The onclick Event</h2>

<p>How to assign on "onclick" event to a p element: </p>

<p id= "demo" onclick="myfunction()">Click me. </p>

<script>
function myfunction(){
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "YOU CLICKED ME!";
}
</script>
</body>
</html>
